# Next Phase: Main Layout & Chat Interface

## Overview
This plan details the architecture and tasks for the next agent session. The goal is to build upon the base component architecture ([BaseComponent](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/ux/tui/components/base.py#6-34), [BaseWidget](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/ux/tui/widgets/base.py#6-33), [BaseLayout](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/ux/tui/layouts/base.py#6-38)) to implement the core conversational interface of the CLI.

## User Review Required
None at this stage. This document serves as a handoff blueprint.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Main Layout
We need a layout container to structure the screen vertically.
- **[NEW]** `agent_cli/ux/tui/layouts/main.py`
  - Extends [BaseLayout](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/ux/tui/layouts/base.py#6-38).
  - Composes the top area (Future Header), middle area (Chat Window), and bottom area (Status Bar / Input Bar).

### 2. Chat Interface Widgets
The core of the application needs to render messages.
- **[NEW]** `agent_cli/ux/tui/widgets/chat_window.py`
  - Extends [BaseWidget](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/ux/tui/widgets/base.py#6-33).
  - A scrollable container that mounts `MessageComponent` instances dynamically as they arrive.
- **[NEW]** `agent_cli/ux/tui/components/message.py`
  - Extends [BaseComponent](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/ux/tui/components/base.py#6-34).
  - Represents a single chat bubble (User or Agent). Should support markdown rendering using Textual's `Markdown` widget internally.

### 3. User Input
An area for the user to type commands or messages to the agent.
- **[NEW]** `agent_cli/ux/tui/widgets/input_bar.py`
  - Extends [BaseWidget](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/ux/tui/widgets/base.py#6-33).
  - Uses Textual's `Input` or `TextArea` component. Dispatches customized `Submit` messages that the [AgentCLIApp](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/ux/tui/app.py#4-39) captures to send to the backend core.

### 4. Status Bar (Refinements)
- **[MODIFY]** [agent_cli/ux/tui/widgets/status_bar.py](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/ux/tui/widgets/status_bar.py)
  - Ensure the StatusBar uses the updated [BaseWidget](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/ux/tui/widgets/base.py#6-33) and horizontal flexbox alignment properly, similar to the previous component fixes.

## Verification Plan
1. Create unit tests for `chat_window.py` and `input_bar.py` checking message propagation.
2. Run `python -m agent_cli` to manually verify the `MainLayout` correctly restricts the Input Bar to the bottom and allows the Chat Window to dynamically scroll in the center.
